main event: Several residents of West Palm Beach, Florida, reported seeing a fiery object streak across the sky on January 27, 1959, shortly after the launch of an Atlas missile from Cape Canaveral.
interesting points: The object had a long, vaporous tail and was seen for about 20 minutes., Reports indicated the object was cigar-shaped with a brilliant illumination., Some witnesses described the object disappearing straight up., There were also separate reports of a ball of fire plunging into Mobile Bay, Alabama., Authorities confirmed no planes crashed and linked the sightings to the Atlas missile launch.
witness description: Several local residents, an aircraft crew, and base personnel reported the sighting.
